# =============================================================================
# Sample crontab for Daily AI Tech News Blog
# =============================================================================
# Install:
#   crontab -e
# then paste a line below, adjusting paths.
#
# Times below are LOCAL TIME of the host. If your server is in UTC and you want
# 08:00 Malaysia time (UTC+8), use 00:00 UTC.
#
# Required env: PATH and OPENAI_API_KEY (cron has a minimal env).
# Easiest pattern: source the project's .env from a wrapper script.

# 08:00 Malaysia time (UTC+8) = 00:00 UTC. Adjust if your server is in MYT.
0 0 * * *   /opt/daily-tech-news/run-daily.sh >> /opt/daily-tech-news/logs/cron.log 2>&1
